            ">Engineering demand </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
          Internet personalities Logan Paul and KSI founded Prime Hydration in 2022. From the get-go, their goal was simple: provide a product that not just quenched thirst but also aligned with the lifestyle and values of its audience. The duo was <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-02-08-2025-reverse-engineering-virality" target="_blank">reverse-engineering virality</a> into a beverage.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px 14px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/ksi-logan-paul-online-success-brand-independence.jpg" alt="KSI and Logan Paul are not wholly dependent on big brands to succeed thanks to their vast online presence" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i>KSI and Logan Paul are not wholly dependent on big brands to succeed thanks to their vast online presence. Credits: 303 London</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
          The mega-influencers leveraged their massive fanbase, which became a built-in advertising engine. Fans felt like they were supporting their idols, and Prime lived and thrived online, launching teasers & countdowns on YouTube, TikTok, and Instagram. They created content around flavor tasting, factories, and label designs, making everyone feel like they were part of the brand. </p> 
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
          Marketed as a hydration drink, Prime came in neon packaging with bold flavors. The focus on health and wellness, combined with an appealing aesthetic, made it a trendy choice among younger consumers. Their exclusive drops ‌sold out repeatedly, making news headlines and trending online. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
         By mid-2022, Prime had secured its biggest traditional credibility through a sponsorship agreement with Arsenal Football Club. Suddenly, this internet-born brand was pitch-side in the Premier League. Prime racked up $250M in global trade in its first year and surged to over $1.2B in 2023. Prime took less than two years to go from an influencer side hustle to an energy drink behemoth.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">The cool walk</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
         When Nicolas Mermoud and Jean-Luc Diard founded HOKA, they wanted to help runners fly downhill faster without wrecking their knees. At that time, lean shoes were all the hype, but HOKA went in the opposite direction. They designed a maximalist running shoe with oversized, cushioned soles with a rocker geometry. HOKA <a 
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-02-08-2025-became-a-cult-favorite" target="_blank">became a cult favorite</a> among elite trail runners who needed durable shoes.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px 14px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/hoka-cloudflyer-orange-foam-innovation.jpg" alt="The introduction of the revolutionary Cloudflyer, with its striking orange foam, further solidified Hoka’s reputation for bold innovation" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            <i> The introduction of the revolutionary Cloudflyer, with its striking orange foam, further solidified Hoka’s reputation for bold innovation. Credits: HOKA</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
         HOKA’s chunky, maximalist shoes went viral as the market was flooded with the post-dad-shoe aesthetic. Fashion influencers and TikTok creators embraced HOKAs for their "normcore" fashion (unisex, average-looking aesthetics) and praised their comfort, using phrases like “walking on clouds.” Aesthetic gym routines, GRWMs (get ready with me), and wellness content often featured them organically. </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
         Over time, high-profile runners, trail athletes, and even non-runners like Gwyneth Paltrow and Reese Witherspoon were spotted wearing HOKAs. With the “<a
style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #8C3321; color: black;" href="https://link.businesshistory.co/bh-02-08-2025-fly-human-fly" target="_blank">Fly Human Fly</a>” slogan, they positioned themselves as a wellness brand. Their victory was based on bridging efficiency and comfort, while also defining internet trends, and the numbers speak for themselves. While the revenue in 2019 was close to $300M, it had grown to $1.4B by 2023. </p>
        </mj-text>
